@* The ASYNC twin of MethodRead (register A14, E_asyncmethodread): the write to `count` happens in an
   `await` continuation. The promotion is decided the same way -- `count` is read by the template-called
   `Format()` and written by `Bump`, so it lifts to a signal regardless of WHERE the write sits. The
   handler is `async () => { await __delay(1); count.value++; }` (decision 119); when the continuation
   runs, the signal write fires the `@Format()` effect and #n advances. *@
<p><span id="n">@Format()</span></p>
<button id="inc" @onclick="Bump">inc</button>

@code {
    private int count = 0;

    private string Format()
    {
        return $"n={count}";
    }

    async Task Bump()
    {
        await Task.Delay(1);
        count++;
    }
}
